[SetUp "1"]

1. --
{ Nominally White is a piece up, but the difference in activity between both sides' forces is simply overwhelming. When teaching young players, who tend to have big respect for the nominal value of the pieces, in such a position I make them observe that White has ten points out of the game! For example, the rook on a1 hardly has the same value as the one on e8, and this is, after all, what development is all about. }
*

