20... Rxd5
{ Black returns some of the material in order to retain his valuable knight, whose departure would leave him very weak on the dark squares; e.g.  20...Be6  21.Bxc6+  bxc6  22.Rxd8+  Qxd8  23.Qxc6+  Bd7  24.Qxa6  e4  25.Re1  with a decisive attack - Naiditsch.   As for the attempt to castle artificially with  20...Kd7  , Naiditsch indicates  21.Be4+   @@StartBracket@@of course not  21.Bxc6+  Kc8  @@EndBracket@@  21...Ke6  22.Bxf5+  Kxf5  23.fxe5  Rxd1+  24.Rxd1  Rd8   @@StartBracket@@not  24...Qxe5  25.Rd5  @@EndBracket@@  25.Rf1+  Ke6  26.Qc4+  Kd7  27.Qg4+  Ke8  28.e6  with a clear advantage. }
