[White "Exercises Chapter 1"]
[Black "Po.Carlsson-E.Blomqvist  Stockholm 2008  Sicilian Defence,  Richter-Rauzer Variation"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "2rqk2r/p2bbp1p/2p1pp2/3p4/2B1P3/2N5/PPPQ1PPP/2KRR3 w k - 0 13"]
[SetUp "1"]

13. exd5 cxd5 14. Bxd5
{ With all the white pieces in ideal locations, and the black king stranded in the centre, the position begs for this kind of sacrifice. }
14... exd5 15. Rxe7+
{ A second sacrifice in order to eliminate Black's main defender.   In contrast,  15.Qxd5  Qc7   @@StartBracket@@or  15.Nxd5  Be6  was less clear@@EndBracket@@. }
15... Kxe7
{ Or if instead  15...Qxe7  , then  16.Nxd5  Qe6  17.Re1  O-O  18.Rxe6  Bxe6  19.Ne7+  and wins. }
16. Nxd5+ Ke6
{ Both alternatives,  16...Kf8  17.Qh6+   @@StartBracket@@and  16...Ke8  17.Nxf6+  @@EndBracket@@ were equally terminal for Black. }
17. Qe3+ Kd6 18. Ne7+ { In view of  18.Ne7+  Kc7  19.Qxa7  , Black resigned. }
