[Black "P.Acs-A.Belezky  German League 2011  French Defence "]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nd7
{ The Rubinstein French is quite popular these days, despite a rather cramped game for Black.   4...Bd7  , followed by ...Bc6, is a different approach. }
5. Nf3 Ngf6 6. Bd3 c5 7. O-O cxd4
{ After the logical  7...Nxe4  8.Bxe4  Nf6  Black also remains under some pressure; e.g.  9.Bg5  cxd4  10.Qe2  , preparing Rad1xd4. }
8. Nxd4 Nc5
{ Black somehow wishes to swap the bishop on d3, but wastes time.   8...Be7  , preparing ...O-O, made much more sense - Baburin. }
9. Bg5
{ Swift development.   9.Nxf6+  gxf6   @@StartBracket@@not  9...Qxf6  10.Nb5  @@EndBracket@@  10.Bb5+  Bd7  11.Qe2  looked promising as well. }
9... h6
{ This is one tempo loss too much.  Correct was   9...Ncxe4  10.Bxe4  Be7  - Baburin. }
10. --
