[SetUp "1"]

10. Bb5+
{ This simple check disrupts Black's development and leaves his king stuck in the centre.   10.Bxf6  gxf6  11.Bb5+  with a transposition, is equally strong. }
10... Ncd7
{ Or  10...Bd7  11.Bxf6  gxf6  12.Nxe6  fxe6  13.Qh5+  and wins - Baburin. }
11. Bxf6 gxf6 12. Qh5
{ Creating the lethal threat of 13. Nxe6 while clearing the first rank for the rooks. In the words of GM Baburin: 'The game is over - Black has only one piece developed - and even that piece can't move!' }
12... Ke7 13. Rad1 Qc7 14. Rfe1
{ The imbalance between attacking and defending pieces is astonishing. } 14...
Ne5 15. Qh4 Bg7 16. Nxf6 { A little combination that destroys Black. } 16...
Bxf6 17. Nf5+ exf5 18. Rxe5+ Qxe5 19. Qb4+ Ke6 20. Bc4+ Qd5 21. Bxd5+ Ke5 22.
f4# *

