1. c4 Nf6 2. Nc3 e6 3. d4 Bb4 4. e3 b6 5. Ne2 Ba6 6. Ng3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 d5 8.
Qf3 O-O 9. e4
{ The current game cast doubt on this gambit.   Nowadays  9.cxd5  is more popular. }
9... dxc4 10. Bg5 h6 11. Bd2
{ 11.e5  seems more consistent; e.g.  11...Qd5  12.Bxf6  Qxf3  13.gxf3  gxf6  14.exf6  Nd7  15.Ne4  with an unclear endgame. }
11... Nbd7 12. e5 Nd5 13. Nf5
{ Too optimistic - in the ensuing complications Black's superior development speaks in his favour.   Preferable was  13.Be2  and O-O in order to conclude development. }
13... exf5 14. Qxd5 Re8 15. Bxc4
{ White is just one move away from O-O with a normal game; however... } 15...
