[SetUp "1"]

15... Nxe5
{ A strong blow that exploits the position of the white king in order to force a superior endgame.   Less promising is  15...Bxc4  16.Qxc4  c5  17.Be3  , followed by O-O. }
16. Qxd8
{ Or  16.dxe5  Qxd5  17.Bxd5  Rxe5+  , regaining the piece with interest. }
16... Nxc4+ 17. Qxe8+ Rxe8+ 18. Kd1 Nxd2 19. Kxd2 Re2+ 20. Kc1 Rxf2
{ Material is about equal, but the difference in activity is devastating. } 21.
g3 Bb7 22. Re1 Be4 { Restricting the white rook is Black's main priority. } 23.
Re3 Rxh2 24. a4 h5
{ Intending ...g7-g5 and ...h5-h4, in order to create a passed pawn. Black won without any difficulty. }
