[White "Exercises Chapter 1"]
[Black "R.Mogranzini-F.Bentivegna  Porto San Giorgio 2011  English Opening"]
[Result "*"]

1. c4 b6 2. Nc3 Bb7 3. e4 e6 4. Nge2
{ White avoids the line  4.d4  Bb4  5.Bd3  f5  and takes the game into English waters. }
4... Nf6 5. d3 c5 6. g3 d5
{ Opening the position when behind in development is always a risky decision.   Safer was  6...d6  7.Bg2  Be7  8.O-O  Nc6  , followed by ...O-O, with a standard Hedgehog game. }
7. exd5 exd5 8. Bg2 Qd7 { An awkward move, but 9. Nf4 was threatening. } 9. Nf4
dxc4 10. Bxb7 Qxb7 11. O-O { Getting the rook to e1 is White's main priority. }
11... cxd3
{ The tempo loss involved in this capture will cost Black dearly.   11...Be7  was called for; e.g.  12.Nfd5  Nxd5  13.Qf3  Nc6  14.Nxd5  O-O-O  and Black defends. }
12. Re1+ Be7
