13. Nfd5
{ Exploiting the pin on the h1-a8 diagonal, White manages to keep the enemy king in the centre.   13.Qxd3  O-O  14.Ncd5  Nc6  was much less convincing. }
13... Nxd5 14. Qf3 Kf8
{ This loses on the spot, but Black had a hard time anyway; e.g.  14...Nc6  15.Nxd5  O-O-O  16.Nxe7+  Nxe7  17.Qxb7+  Kxb7  18.Rxe7+  Kc6  19.Bd2  with a winning endgame for White. }
