1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c5 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. e4 g6 7. f4 Bg7 8. e5
{ This is a very principled approach against the Modern Benoni.   8.Bb5+  , checking Black's reply before going e4-e5, is the main line. }
8... dxe5 9. fxe5 Nfd7 10. e6 fxe6 11. dxe6 Qe7 12. Nd5 Qxe6+ 13. Qe2
{ Interestingly, the queen exchange favours White, whereas  13.Be2  Na6  is less promising. }
13... Qxe2+ 14. Bxe2 Be5
{ While  14...Na6  now fails to  15.Bxa6  bxa6  16.Nc7+   The active  14...O-O  15.Nc7  Nc6  16.Nxa8  Nb4  was called for, with counterplay - Yusupov. }
15. Nf3 Nf6 16. Bc4 Nxd5 17. Bxd5 Bf6 18. O-O Nc6
