13. Nd6+ { A strong sacrifice that opens the gates to Black's king. } 13...
exd6 14. exd6 Qb4 15. Qe2+ Kd8 16. Bd2 Bb7
{ Unfortunately for Black,  16...Bxd6  runs into  17.Ne4  Qb6  18.Nxd6  Qxd6  19.Ba5+ }
17. O-O-O Nf6 18. Rhe1 Bxd6
{ This virtually means returning the piece, making White's practical task considerably easier.  For better or worse,   18...Qb6  had to be tried, when Rybka suggests the curious continuation  19.Na4  Qb5  20.Qe5  Qxa4  21.Qxc5  Qc6  22.Ba5+  Kc8  23.Qe5  Bxd6  24.Rxd6  Qb5  25.Rd5  d6   @@StartBracket@@not  25...Nxd5  26.Qe8+  @@EndBracket@@  26.Rxd6  Qxe5  27.Rxe5  with a strong initiative even into the endgame. }
19. Ne4 Bf4 { Obviously  19...Qb6  20.Nxd6  Qxd6  failed to  21.Ba5+ } 20. Bxf4
Nxe4 21. fxe4 Re8 22. Qg4
{ This double attack breaks through Black's defences. } 22... Re6 23. Qxg7 Bc6
24. Qf8+ Re8 25. Qxf7 { In this hopeless position, Black resigned. } *

