12. O-O-O
{ Setting up the threat of 13.Rhe1+ and at the same time seizing the d-file.   Less promising is  12.Bb5  Qe6+  13.Be3  cxb2   @@StartBracket@@or  12.Ne5  Nxe5  13.Bb5  Bd7  14.Bxc6  Bxc6  15.Qc2  cxb2  16.Rb1  Bxg2  with counterplay@@EndBracket@@ - Taimanov. }
12... cxb2+
{ After  12...Qxa4  13.Rhe1+  Be7  14.Rxe7+  Kf8  15.Rxf7+  Kg8  16.Rfxd7+  Qxc4  17.Rd8+  Kf7  18.Ne5+  White wins. }
