12. c5
{ A strong sacrifice, which prepares Nc4 with the focus on Black's weak point d6. }
12... dxc5
{ On  12...bxc5   @@StartBracket@@ or  12...Nxc5  @@EndBracket@@ there follows the same reply. }
13. Nc4 e5 14. f4 { Striking while the iron is hot. The check on d6 can wait. }
14... Bc6
{ This bishop will be fatally diverted from the long diagonal.   The last chance was  14...a6  15.Nbd6+  Bxd6  16.Nxd6+  Ke7  and Black is still alive. }
15. fxe5 Bxb5 16. exf6 Bxc4 17. e5
{ White's game plays itself. The threat is 18. Qf3, winning the exchange. }
17... a6 18. Qg4 gxf6 { Unfortunately for Black  18...Be6  runs into  19.fxg7 }
19. Qxc4 fxe5 20. Rf1 f6 21. Qe6+ Kd8 22. Rd1
{ In view of the double threats at d7 and f6, Black resigned. } *

