{ Instead of accepting the Benko with  6.bxa6   @@StartBracket@@or handing over the pawn by  6.b6  , White launches his own gambit.@@EndBracket@@ }
6... Nxe4 7. Qc2 f5
{ A risky move due to the weakening of the light squares around Black's king.   7...Nf6  8.Qxc5  d6  9.Qd4  Bg7  , followed by ...O-O, seems preferable, in the same spirit of development above material. }
8. Nbd2 Nf6
{ Aware that  8...Nxd2  9.Bxd2  d6  10.Bc3  is horrible for him, Black surrenders the c5-pawn and starts pressurizing the one on  d5  . }
9. Qxc5 d6 10. Qd4 Bb7 11. Bc4 axb5 12. Bxb5+ Nbd7 13. O-O
