13. exd4
{ Much better was  13.Ne4  Nxe4  14.Bxe4  dxe3  15.O-O  exf2+  16.Qxf2  with compensation - Beliavsky. }
13... Re8+ 14. Kf1
{ After  14.Ne2  Bb4+  15.Bc3  Bf5  Black also enjoys a strong initiative.   Instead,  14.Be2  Bg4  15.f3  Bh5  16.O-O  , securing the king, seems preferable, although  16...Qc7  17.h3  Bg6  18.Bd3  Nh5  keeps the initiative for Black - Korchnoi. }
14... Qa5 15. Qd1 Bb4 16. Rc1 Bd7 17. a3 Bxc3 18. Rxc3 Nd5 19. Bxd5
{ Not  19.Rc5  Bb5+  20.Kg1  Re1+  and wins - Beliavsky. } 19... Qxd5
{ Despite the simplifications Black keeps a clear initiative thanks to superior activity. }
20. a4 Rac8 21. f3 Rxc3 22. Bxc3 Re3
{ Now that  22...Re3  23.Qd2  runs into  23...Rxf3+  White loses both his queenside pawns. }
