[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Exercises Chapter 1"]
[Black "P.Svidler-S.Volkov  Russian Championship,  Krasnoyarsk 2003  French Defence"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Qb6 5. Nf3 Bd7
{ A flexible line in the Advance French. By postponing ...Nc6 Black keeps the option of a later ...Bb5, swapping his 'bad' bishop. }
6. a3 a5 { White is denied the space-gaining b2-b4. } 7. b3
{ Preparing to meet ...a5-a4 by b3-b4, keeping the pawn structure intact. }
7... Na6 8. Be3 Rc8 9. Bd3 Ne7
{ Having overprotected the sensitive c5-pawn, Black starts bringing out his kingside pieces. }
10. O-O
{ Or  10.dxc5  Nxc5  11.Bc2  Qa6  preventing White's castling - Svidler. }
10... Nf5 11. Bxf5 exf5 12. Re1 c4
{ The prophylactic  12...Be6  was preferable. } 13. --
{ Your move. ..@@StartBracket@@The exercise starts on the next variation@@EndBracket@@ }
