[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Exercises Chapter 1"]
[Black "P.Svidler-S.Volkov  Russian Championship,  Krasnoyarsk 2003  French Defence"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "2r1kb1r/1p1b1ppp/nq6/p2pPp2/2pP4/PPP1BN2/5PPP/RN1QR1K1 w k - 0 13"]
[SetUp "1"]

13. bxc4 Rxc4
{ Not  13...dxc4  14.d5  Bc5  15.e6  fxe6  16.Ne5  , intending  16...--  17.Qh5+  , with a huge initiative. }
14. e6 Bxe6 15. Ne5
{ For the price of a mere pawn, White has obtained a strong knight in the centre and cleared the e-file for a future attack. }
15... Rc7 16. Qa4+
{ An annoying check that forces Black to leave his king stranded in the centre.   16.c4  f6  17.Qh5+  Kd8  was less promising - Svidler. }
16... Kd8 17. c4
{ A tempting advance;   but the simple  17.Nd2  was even stronger; e.g.  17...f6   @@StartBracket@@or  17...Rxc3  18.Ndf3  , followed by Bd2@@EndBracket@@  18.Rab1  Qd6  19.Nd3  Qxa3  20.Qb5  with moves like Bf4 and Nf4 hanging in the air. }
17... f6 18. c5 Qb2 19. Nd3 Qxa1 20. Qxa5 Qa2
{ Black returns the favour.   By  20...Bc8  preparing ...b7-b6, he could have kept the balance; e.g.  21.Nd2  b6  22.cxb6  Qxa3  23.bxc7+  Nxc7  24.Qb6  Qa6  25.Qb3  and White has compensation for the pawn, but nothing more - Svidler. }
21. Bf4 Qc4 22. Nb4 Ke8
{ Black correctly returns the rook in order to save his king. } 23. Bxc7 Kf7
24. Qb6 Bc8 25. Nxa6 Qxa6
{ The ensuing endgame is lost for Black, so the capture  25...bxa6  was the last chance. }
26. Qxa6 bxa6 27. Nc3 Be6 28. Rb1
{ Preparing Rb7, with a decisive advantage thanks to the strong passed pawn and the superior activity.   The game continued  28.Rb1  Be7  29.Rb7  Re8  30.f3  g5  31.Ra7  f4  32.Bd6  Kf8  33.Rxa6  Bxd6  34.Rxd6  Bf7  35.Nxd5  Re1+  36.Kf2  and White went on to win. }
