[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Exercises Chapter 1"]
[Black "A.Vovk-M.Kowara  Warsaw (rapid) 2009  Sicilian Defence, Kan Variation"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "B3kb1r/2q2ppp/4p1n1/1p2P1B1/8/8/1PP2PPP/3Q1RK1 b k - 0 17"]
[SetUp "1"]

17... Be7
{ Speeding up development while neutralizing White's mating idea.   17...Bc5  in the same spirit, fails to  18.Bc6+  and the bishop is untouchable because of mate.   Whereas the game continued  17...Nxe5  18.Qe2  Qb8   @@StartBracket@@ The last chance was  18...f6  19.Qxb5+  Kf7  , followed by ...Bd6 @@EndBracket@@  19.Qxe5  and Black resigned in view of  19...Qxe5   @@StartBracket@@or  19...Qxa8  20.Qxb5+  @@EndBracket@@  20.Bc6 }
18. Bxe7 Kxe7
{ Clearing the back rank for the rook. Black has nothing to worry about; e.g.  18...Kxe7  19.Qf3  Nxe5  20.Qa3+  Qd6  21.Qa7+  Kf6  followed by ...Rd8. }
