[FEN "3q1rk1/1pp2ppp/8/r2b4/1bBn4/1PN2PP1/3Q1K1P/1RB3NR w - - 0 17"]
[SetUp "1"]

17. Qxd4
{ Giving back some material in order to repel the enemy attack.   Both:  -  17.Bxd5  Rxd5  , preparing ...Re8   - And  17.Qd3  Bc6  18.Be3  Nf5  19.Qxd8  Rxd8  , with the threat of  20.--  20...b5  , would have let Black retain the initiative. }
17... Bc5 18. Qxc5 Rxc5 19. Nxd5 b5
{ Stronger than  19...Rxd5  20.Bxd5  Qxd5  , when White manages to consolidate his slight material plus by  21.Ne2  followed by  21...--  22.Re1 }
20. Ba3 bxc4 21. Bxc5 Qxd5 22. Bxf8
{ The winning attempt  22.b4  proves risky after  22...Qd2+  23.Ne2  Re8  24.Rhe1  h6  preparing  25.--  25...c3  ;   but not  24...c3  25.Rbd1  when  25...Rxe2+  fails to  26.Rxe2  Qxd1  27.Re8 }
22... Qd4+ 23. Kg2
{ Draw agreed, in view of  23.Kg2  Qd2+  24.Kh3  Qh6+  25.Kg2  Qd2+  etc. } *

