[SetUp "1"]

19. Ke2 { Forcing favourable simplifications. } 19... Nxg2
{ After  19...Qb5+  20.Kxe3  O-O-O  21.Bf1  Black's compensation is insufficient; e.g.  21...Qb6+  22.Ke2  Nd4+  23.Ke1  Rhe8  24.Bd3  Rxe5+  25.Kf1  , followed by Kg2. }
20. Qxb6 axb6 21. Kf2
{ White regains the piece and emerges a sound pawn up in the endgame. } 21...
Nh4 22. gxh4 Ke7 23. Rhg1 Rhg8 24. --
{ At this point, the game continued  24.Rg4  h5  25.Re4  Ke6  26.a3  Rad8  , followed by ...Ne7-d5, and Black finally saved a draw.   By  24.a3  , preparing Rad1, White could have maintained his advantage; e.g.  24...Ra4  25.Kg3  Ke6  26.Rad1  , when  26...Nxe5  fails to  27.Rge1  f6  28.f4  . }
