[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Exercises Chapter 1"]
[Black "G.Flear-R.Vera Gonzalez  Elgoibar 1994  Semi-Slav Defence"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1b1k2r/pp1nnppp/4p3/4N3/2P5/B7/PP1QBPqP/2KR4 b kq - 0 14"]
[SetUp "1"]

14... O-O
{ Returning some of the material in order to secure the king.   Less practical was  14...Qxh2  15.Nxd7  Qc7  16.Bxe7  Qxd7  17.Bd6  and Black's king stays in the centre.   While  14...Nd5  15.cxd5  Nxe5  16.Qb4  Qg5+  17.f4  Qd8  18.fxe5  seems even less appealing for him. }
15. Bxe7
{ After  15.Nxd7  Bxd7  16.Qxd7  Nf5  17.Bxf8  Rxf8  only Black can be better. }
15... Nxe5 16. Bxf8 Bd7
{ Bringing out the pieces. By now Black's safer king and extra pawn compensate for White's bishop pair and superior activity. }
17. Bb4 Be8
{ Vera suggests  17...Qxf2  18.Bc3  f6  19.Bxe5  fxe5  20.Qxd7  Qxe2  21.Qxe6+  Kh8  with a slight advantage, so probably 17. Bc5 was more accurate on the previous move. }
18. Qe3 Nc6 19. Bd6 Rd8 20. h4 e5
{ Draw agreed, in view of  20...e5  21.Bxe5  Rxd1+  22.Bxd1  Nxe5  23.Qxe5  Qc6  with an equal endgame. @@StartBracket@@End of Chapter One@@EndBracket@@ }
