4. exf5
{ This, admittedly, helps Black's development but, more importantly, it facilitates an attack on the weakened light squares in his camp.   In the same spirit,  4.Bd3  is also strong.   In contrast, the game saw  4.e5  dxe5  5.dxe5  Qxd1+  6.Nxd1  Nfd7  7.Nf3  Nc6  with rough equality. }
4... Bxf5 5. Bd3
{ Simple and strong: the exchange of these bishops will make the weakness on e6 more strongly felt. }
5... Qd7 6. Nf3
{ Preparing O-O and Re1. Black's position already looks difficult; } 6... --
{ e.g.  6...Nc6  7.O-O  O-O-O  8.d5  Nb4  9.Bxf5  Qxf5  10.Nd4  , heading for e6. }
