[SetUp "1"]

11. Bh3
{ One of several good choices, increasing the pressure at d7.   Also interesting was  11.Bg5  , setting up the threat 12. Nd6; e.g.  11...Bg7  12.Nd6+  Kf8  13.Nxb7  Qc7  14.Qc6  with some advantage.   As well as  11.d6  exd6  12.Bc4  Be7  13.O-O  , when  13...Nf6  fails to  14.Nxf6+  Bxf6  15.Bh6  , followed by Rfe1+.   In contrast, the game went  11.Bb5  a6  12.Bg5   @@StartBracket@@  12.Bxd7+  Qxd7  13.Qd4  was correct, keeping the initiative.@@EndBracket@@  13...axb5  13.Nd6+  exd6  14.Bxd8  bxa4  and Black won. }
11... f5
{ It is difficult to find a defence; e.g.  11...Bg7  12.Nc5  Nf6  13.Bg5  , winning material   While both:  11...a6  12.O-O  b5  13.Qd4  Ndf6  14.d6   And  11...Nf6  12.Nxf6+  exf6  13.O-O  , preparing Re1+, are equally bad for Black. }
12. Ng5 { Intending Ne6 with a huge advantage. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Exercises Chapter 2"]
[Black "J.Sanaguano-O.Vaca  Riobamba 2010  French Defence"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5
{ The Exchange Variation is hardly a critical test of the French, and the way in which White treats it in this game is probably more suited against the Caro-Kann. }
3... exd5 4. Bd3 Nf6 5. h3 Be7 6. Nf3 O-O 7. O-O Nbd7
{ Another good option was  7...c5  , followed by ...Nc6. } 8. Re1 c5 9. dxc5
{ Liberating the black pieces.   9.c3  , stabilizing the centre, was preferable. }
9... Nxc5 10. Bf1
{ In the IQP structure almost any exchange favours the side playing against it, so  10.Bg5  or  10.Nc3  was better, not fearing  10...Nxd3  . }
10... Bd7 11. Bg5 Bc6 12. Nd4
{ Of course the idea of blocking the IQP isn't bad, but in this particular position  12.Nc3  or  12.Nbd2  made more sense, in order to play with all the pieces. }
12... Nce4 13. Bh4
{ A rather indifferent move. The correct retreat was  13.Be3  , and we will soon see the difference. }
13... --
{ How to punish White? @@StartBracket@@The exercise starts on the next variation@@EndBracket@@ }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Exercises Chapter 2"]
