[SetUp "1"]

10. Nb5
{ Attacking Black's weak point, the d6-pawn. By the way, this was already a good option on the ninth move.   In contrast, the game went  10.Be3  O-O  11.a3  d5  12.e5  Nf5  with balanced chances. }
10... Qb8
{ Or  10...Nc8  11.Bf4  e5  12.dxe5  dxe5  13.Bg5  f6  14.Be3  with a strong initiative, now that  14...O-O  fails to  15.Qd5+  Kh8  16.Rad1  . }
11. Bf4 Nc8 { Obviously  11...e5  runs into  12.dxe5  dxe5  13.Nd6+  . } 12. d5
{ White hurries to clear the centre before Black castles. } 12... exd5 13. Qxd5
O-O { There is nothing better. } 14. Nxd6
{ Winning a pawn, with a huge advantage. } *

