[White "Exercises Chapter 2"]
[Black "H.Llamuca-A.Briceño  Santo Domingo 2010  Bishop’s Opening "]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 Nf6 3. d3 d5
{ A rather risky reply to the Bishop's Opening.   Either  3...Nc6  or  3...c6  , preparing ...d7-d5, is more common. }
4. exd5 Nxd5 5. Nf3 Nc6 6. O-O Be6
{ Black should prefer the gambit line  6...Be7  7.Re1  Nb6  8.Bb3  Bg4  9.h3  Bh5  10.g4  Bg6  11.Nxe5  Nxe5  12.Rxe5  O-O  , when White's weakened kingside structure at least implies some compensation for the pawn. }
7. Re1 { Preparing a direct attack on e5.   7.Ng5  was another good option. }
7... Bd6
{ How to punish Black? @@StartBracket@@The exercise starts on the next variation@@EndBracket@@ }
