10... Nc6
{ Preparing a counterstrike on the weakened e1-h4 diagonal.  10...Ng6  11.f5  Ne4  in the same spirit is also strong.   In contrast, the game saw  10...Qc7  11.fxe5  Bxe5  12.Ba4+  and White went on to win. }
11. f5 Ne4
{ Setting up the mortal threat of  12.--  12...Qh4+  . Also interesting is  11...Bg3+  12.Kf1  O-O  13.fxe6  fxe6  14.Nf3  e5  with ample compensation. }
12. Bxe4 { Or  12.fxe6  Qh4+  13.Kd1  Nf2+  14.Kd2  Bf4+  and wins. } 12...
Bg3+ 13. Kf1 dxe4 14. fxe6 fxe6
{ 15.--  15...O-O+  next, Black recovers the piece while keeping the attack. }
15. -- { Obviously  15.Qxe4  at this point fails to the reply  15...Qd1+  . } *

