[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Nge7 6. Na3 Bd7
{ This bishop move often makes sense in the Advance Variation; although on the present occasion,  6...cxd4  7.cxd4  Nf5  is more usual. }
7. Bg5
{ Setting up the dangerous threat of 7. Nb5.   A more methodical choice is  7.Nc2  , followed by Bd3. }
7... Qb6
{ Aware that both  7...h6  and  7...cxd4  run into  8.Nb5  , Black unpins his knight, but this soon leads him into new difficulties.   7...a6  , preventing Nb5, was correct; }
8. --
{ How to punish Black? @@StartBracket@@The exercise starts on the next variation@@EndBracket@@ }
