[SetUp "1"]

8. dxc5
{ Initiating favourable complications.   In contrast, after  8.Nb5  Ng6  Black is perfectly ok. }
8... Qxc5 { Or  8...Qxb2  9.Nb5  with decisive threats. } 9. Nb5 Nxe5
{ This won't end well, but Black had no other defence against the double threat at c7 and d6. }
10. Nxe5 Bxb5 11. Be3 d4 12. Qxd4
{ Of course not  12.Bxd4  Qd5  13.c4  Qe4+  and Black is alive.   After the text, he had instead to resign, in view of  12.Qxd4  Qxd4  13.Bxb5+  . }
