[Round "?"]
[White "Exercises Chapter 2"]
[Black "B.Lalic-B.Laurent  Metz 2007  Benoni Defence"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c5 4. d5 d6 5. e4 exd5 6. cxd5
{ At this point, most Benoni players play 6...g6 without any thinking, but Laurent has an independent idea in mind. }
6... a6
{ With  6...a6  , by means of the 'threat' of ...b7-b5, Black aims to provoke  7.a4  , when after  7...g6  he has managed to sidestep the sharp line   i.e.  6...g6  7.f4  Bg7  8.Bb5+  . However, Lalic has other intentions. }
7. f4 b5 { 7...Qe7  was preferable, trying to stop e4-e5 - Baburin. } 8. e5 b4
{ A fatal miscalculation.   For better or worse, Black had to try  8...Qe7  9.Qe2  Nfd7  . }
9. --
{ How to punish Black? @@StartBracket@@The exercise starts on the next variation@@EndBracket@@ }
