[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Exercises Chapter 2"]
[Black "W.Lombardy-V.Smyslov  Teesside 1975  Vienna Game"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 d5 4. d3
{ An insipid version of the Vienna Game.   4.fxe5  Nxe4  5.Nf3  or  5.Qf3  is more to the point. }
4... exf4 5. e5 { A lesser evil was  5.Bxf4  , speeding up development. } 5...
d4
{ By this counterblow Black grabs the initiative.   5...Ng4  6.Bxf4  was less ambitious. }
6. Nce2 Nd5 7. Nxf4 Bb4+ { An annoying check. } 8. Kf2
{ The natural  8.Bd2  runs into  8...Ne3  . } 8... Nc6 9. Nf3 O-O 10. Be2
{ With his last two moves White is finally taking care of his development, but it is a bit too late.How to punish White? @@StartBracket@@The exercise starts on the next variation@@EndBracket@@ }
