[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Exercises Chapter 2"]
[Black "W.Lange-E.J.Diemer  Weidenau 1937  Dutch Defence "]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "rnb1k2r/pp2n1pp/2pbpq2/3p1p2/2PP4/2NBPN2/PP3PPP/R1BQ1RK1 w kq - 0 8"]
[SetUp "1"]

8. e4
{ Exploiting the tactical motif  8.e4  dxe4  9.Bxe4  fxe4  10.Nxe4  , White achieves a favourable opening of the centre. }
8... dxe4 9. Bxe4 e5
{ This further opening of the position is definitely not to Black's benefit, considering his delay in development.   Instead, after  9...Ng6  10.Bc2  O-O  11.Re1  White enjoys a clear plus thanks to his superior pawn structure, but the battle goes on. }
10. dxe5 Bxe5 11. Bg5 { Development with tempo. } 11... Qd6 12. Nxe5 Qxd1
{ Or  12...Qxe5  13.Bf3  , followed by 14. Re1 - Neishtadt. } 13. Raxd1 fxe4
14. Nxe4 { The rest is just agony for Black. } 14... Nd7 15. Nd6+ Kf8 16. Bxe7+
Kxe7 17. Nxc8+ *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Exercises Chapter 2"]
[Black "G.Bastrikov-I.Kogan  Minsk 1971  Sicilian Defence, Najdorf Variation"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 e6 7. Qf3
{ Preparing a quick O-O-O.   The main option in this heavily debated Najdorf line is  7.f4  . }
7... Nbd7
{ There is an argument in favour of including  7...h6  8.Bh4  - then White's ninth move in the game becomes impossible due to ...g7-g5. }
8. O-O-O Qc7 9. Qg3 b5 10. Bd3 Bb7 11. Rhe1
{ After just 11 moves, White has concluded development and is now ready for an attack on Black's king. }
11... h6
{ This move is badly timed.   11...Be7  , getting on with development, was preferable. }
12. Bxf6 { Exchanging a main defender and gaining time for the attack. } 12...
Nxf6
{ A big mistake.   After  12...gxf6  13.Qh3  , intending 14. Nxe6, Black is under some pressure, but the game will present him with worse problems. }
13. --
{ How to punish Black? @@StartBracket@@The exercise starts on the next variation@@EndBracket@@ }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Exercises Chapter 2"]
[Black "G.Bastrikov-I.Kogan  Minsk 1971  Sicilian Defence, Najdorf Variation"]
