13. e5
{ A key move, opening the gates to Black's king before he manages to castle. }
13... dxe5
{ After  13...Nd5  14.Nxe6  fxe6  15.exd6  Qxd6  16.Qg6+  Kd7  17.Rxe6  White's attack is decisive. }
14. Ncxb5 Qb6
{ Or  14...axb5  15.Bxb5+  , when both  15...Nd7   @@StartBracket@@and  15...Ke7  16.Nf5+  exf5  17.Rxe5+  @@EndBracket@@  16.Nxe6  fxe6  17.Qg6+  Ke7  18.Rxd7+  win for White - Neishtadt. }
15. Nxe6 fxe6 16. Bg6+ Ke7 17. Qa3+ Qc5 18. Qxc5# *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Exercises Chapter 2"]
[Black "Bugay-Malkin  Baranovichi 1971  Sicilian Defence,  Taimanov Variation"]
[Result "*"]

1. c4 e6 2. Nc3 c5 3. e4 Nc6 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. d4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 Bb4
{ The most active choice, immediately challenging White's Maroczy Bind. } 7. f3
{ Bugay proceeds as if nothing had happened.   7.Nxc6  bxc6  8.Bd3  , followed by O-O, is preferable in order to speed up development. }
7... d5 { Refuting White's opening play. } 8. cxd5 exd5 9. Bb5
{ After  9.Bg5  h6  10.Bh4  dxe4  11.Nxc6  Qxd1+  and 12...bxc6 Black also has an excellent game. }
9... O-O
{ Sacrificing a pawn to speed up development.   9...Bd7  10.Bxc6  bxc6  11.e5  is less promising. }
10. Nxc6
{ Too materialistic.   10.O-O  was called for; e.g.  10...Bc5  11.Bxc6  dxe4  12.Be3  bxc6  13.Nxe4  and White is still alive. }
10... bxc6 11. Bxc6
{ How to punish White? @@StartBracket@@The exercise starts on the next variation@@EndBracket@@ }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Exercises Chapter 2"]
[Black "Bugay-Malkin  Baranovichi 1971  Sicilian Defence,  Taimanov Variation"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bq1rk1/p4ppp/2B2n2/3p4/1b2P3/2N2P2/PP4PP/R1BQK2R b KQ - 0 11"]
[SetUp "1"]

11... Nxe4
{ A strong sacrifice, exploiting the vulnerable e1-h4 diagonal as well as White's lack of development. }
12. fxe4 { Or  12.Bxa8  Qh4+  13.g3  Nxg3  with overwhelming threats. } 12...
Qh4+ 13. Kd2
{ Both  13.g3  Qxe4+   and  13.Kf1  Qf6+  , followed by ...Qxc6, were equally bad for White. }
13... Bg4 { Another piece joins the party, with decisive effect. } 14. Qa4 Qf2+
15. Kd3 dxe4+ 16. Kc4 Rab8 { In view of the multiple threats, White resigned. }
