1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Bg2 dxc4
{ Another option is  4...Be7  5.O-O  O-O  , when White can play a Reti with  6.b3   Or enter the Catalan after  6.d4  . }
5. Qa4+ Nbd7
{ The alternative was a Meran set-up with  5...c6  6.Qxc4  b5  7.Qc2  Bb7  , followed by ...Nbd7 and ...c6-c5. }
6. Qxc4 c5 7. Qb3 Rb8 { Both  7...b6  8.Ne5 } 8. d3 Bd6
{ and  8...b6  9.Bf4  were premature. } 9. a4 b6
{ After preparing twice for this move Black is finally ready to deploy the queen's bishop on the long diagonal. }
10. Nc3 a6 11. Ng5 Bb7 { Black avoids the trap  11...O-O  12.Nxe6  . } 12. Nce4
{ Starting active operations with both knights.How do you defend with Black? @@StartBracket@@The exercise starts on the next variation@@EndBracket@@ }
