[SetUp "1"]

17... O-O-O
{ This was a much better choice than the game - Postny.   17...O-O  18.Bc1  Rae8  19.Nf3  e6  A logical try to create counterplay in the centre. Unfortunately White won't capture on e6, nor will he recapture on d5 with the c-pawn in Benoni-style, but with the e-pawn, after which most of the black pieces will remain in the margins of the battle.  20.Qc2  Re7  21.h3  exd5  22.exd5  Rfe8  The control of the open file is irrelevant in this case, and White can just keep on attacking.  23.f5  gxf5   23...Nf8  @@StartBracket@@Or  24.fxg6  fxg6  25.Nh4  @@EndBracket@@  24.Nh4  Ne5  25.Nxf5  Rd7  26.Nxg7  Swapping a main defender of Black's kingside.  26...Kxg7  27.Qd2  Rh8  28.Qg5+  Ng6  29.b3  In view of 30. Bb2+ coming up, Black resigned. }
