[Black "Exercise #1: L.Van Wely-S.Karjakin"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1b1k2r/1p1n2p1/p1pbp2p/q2p1p2/P1PPn2B/2NBPN2/1PQ2PPP/R4RK1 w kq - 0 12"]
[SetUp "1"]

12. c5
{ Before taking charge of the knight on e4, Van Wely fixes the queenside pawn structure, in order to rule out a possible ...c6-c5 break, and enables a future Nd2-c4 manoeuvre.   In effect, after  12.Bxe4  dxe4  13.Nd2  c5  Black wouldn't have anything to complain about. }
12... Bb8 13. Bxe4
{ Swapping the least active minor piece for the strong enemy knight. } 13...
fxe4
{ By now,  13...dxe4  14.Nd2  , followed by Nc4 and Bg3, would yield White a clear grip on the dark squares. }
14. Nd2 O-O 15. f3
{ A key move to break the enemy pawn chain and clear the f-file before Black's queenside pieces join the battle. }
