1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 d5 3. cxd5 Qxd5
{ Black's second move surrendered the centre without getting anything in return, and here  3...Nxd5  was more to the point, avoiding the early exposure of the queen. }
4. Nc3 Qd8 5. Nf3 e6 6. e4 Be7 7. Bc4 { 7.Bd3  O-O  8.Qe2 } 7... c6 8. O-O Nbd7
9. Re1 O-O 10. a3 b5 11. Ba2 a6 12. Bg5 Bb7 13. Rc1 h6 14. Bh4 Re8
