[SetUp "1"]

15. Ne3 { Redirecting the knight to the central post on d5. } 15... Qa5 16. Nd5
Rd7 { Unable to accomplish ...e7-e6, Black opts for a few useful moves. } 17.
h3 Rc8 18. Bg5
{ An annoying move for Black since any defence of the e7-pawn implies some kind of concession, besides which f2-f4 might be in the air. }
18... Bxd5 19. exd5 c4 20. h4
{ Preparing Bh3. Thanks to the bishop pair and the semi-open e-file, White already possesses a slight advantage. }
20... Re8 21. Qe4 h6
{ This leads to unfavourable complications.   21...b5  , preparing ...Nd3, was probably a lesser evil. }
22. Bxh6 Nd3 23. Bxg7 Nxe1 24. Bd4 Nd3 25. h5
{ Initiating a strong attack.  The game continued   25.h5  Qa6  26.Qh4  f5  27.hxg6  Qxg6  28.Bf3  , preparing Bh5, and White went on to win. }
