1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. f4
{ Quite a rare, but far from insipid, line against the Alekhine. } 4... dxe5 5.
fxe5 c5 6. c4
{ But this pawn advance is badly timed, in contrast to the Four Pawns Attack which we saw in Van der Wiel-Vaganian.   Instead, with  6.Nf3  cxd4  7.Qxd4  Nc6  8.Qe4  , White could still fight for an edge. }
6... Nb4 7. d5
{ One more inaccuracy.   7.a3  N4c6  8.e6  was more in the spirit of the variation. }
7... Bf5 8. Na3
