8... e6
{ By means of the double threat of ...exd5 and ...Qh4+, Black destroys the enemy centre. }
9. Qa4+
{ There is nothing better; e.g.  9.d6  Qh4+  , followed by one more queen check. }
9... Qd7 10. Qxd7+ Nxd7 11. Nf3
{ Or  11.dxe6  Nxe5  12.exf7+  Kxf7  , followed by ...Ned3+, with a huge lead in development. }
11... exd5 12. cxd5 Nxd5 13. Bc4 N7b6 14. Bb5+ Bd7
{ Having a sound extra pawn, Black went on to win. } *

