[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 Nf6 3. cxd5 Qxd5 4. Nc3 Qd8 5. Nf3 e6 6. e4 Be7 7. Bd3 h6
{ A loss of time as well as a weakening of Black's kingside structure.   7...b6  at once was a lesser evil. }
8. O-O b6 9. Qe2 Bb7 10. Rd1
{ Such a set-up is quite logical in this structure, in order to support the pawn centre with two major pieces and complicate Black's ...c7-c5. }
10... Nbd7
{ The immediate  10...O-O  would have run into  11.e5  Nd5  12.Qe4  , when Black's inaccuracy on move seven makes itself felt. }
11. Bc2 c6 12. Bf4 Nh5
{ This won't end well, but it was already hard to give Black good advice. } 13.
