14. d5
{ A strong advance that opens the position to the benefit of White's better developed forces.   14.e5  g6  15.g4  Ng7  was rather less promising. }
14... Nhf6
{ After  14...e5  15.Rac1   Or  14...exd5  15.exd5  cxd5  16.Nd4  Black is also in trouble. }
15. dxe6 fxe6 16. e5
{ The most forcing choice; although the methodical  16.Nd4  Nf8  17.Bb3  Qc8  18.Rac1  was strong as well.   16.e5  has the point that  16...Nd5  runs into  17.Bg6+  , so Black accepts the offer. }
