1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. e4 Nxc3 6. bxc3 Bg7 7. Bc4 O-O 8.
Ne2 Nc6
{ Quite a popular deviation from the thematic 8...c5. Black aims at light square play with ...Na5, ...b7-b6, ...Bb7 etc, while the central break ...e7-e5 can also be considered. }
9. O-O Qd7
{ An awkward move at first sight, but since the queen's bishop is heading for b7, the queen will prove well placed on d7. }
10. Ba3
{ The bishop isn't doing much there.   10.Be3  , followed by Qd2, is a more popular choice. }
10... Na5 11. Bd3 b6 12. Nf4
{ 12.Rb1  Bb7  13.d5  c6  14.c4  was preferable - Moiseev. } 12... Bb7 13. Qe2
Rfd8 14. Rad1 e6 15. e5
{ Exposing the central pawns.   The modest  15.Bb4  Nc6  16.Ba3  was better - Moiseev. }
15... --
