[SetUp "1"]

17... b5
{ An excellent counterstrike, exploiting the fact that the knight on c3 is tied to the e4-pawn.   17...cxb4  18.axb4  b5  is less dynamic, when  19.cxb5  axb5  20.Rc1  keeps the balance. }
18. h4
{ Since  18.cxb5  axb5  19.Bxb5  Bxb5+  20.Nxb5  Nxe4  is completely impossible, White just ignores Black's queenside expansion and carries on with his attack, even at the cost of a pawn. }
18... bxc4 19. Bc2 cxb4 20. axb4 Rab8
{ Now it is evident that Black's attack is faster. } 21. h5 Rxb4 22. hxg6 fxg6
23. Rh1 Rb2
{ Wisely enough, both here and on the next move Black avoids  23...Nxg4  24.Bxg7+  Kxg7  25.Rxg4  , followed by 26. Qh6+. }
24. Kd1 Qa5 25. Ng5 Nxg4
{ Ivkov has seen that receiving a check on h7 isn't a serious matter when his own attack is close to success. }
26. Bxg7+ Kxg7 27. Rxh7+ Kg8 28. Qc1 Bxg5 29. Qxg5 Qa1+ *

