13. Nb5
{ The start of an excellent strategical operation, with the objective of installing a knight on d6.   13.e5  Nd5  was rather less convincing. }
13... c6 { In the event of  13...c5  White can just react as in the game. } 14.
e5 Nd5 15. Qe4 { 15.Bxe7  Rxe7  16.Nd6  first was even simpler. } 15... Nf8
{ Or  15...f5  16.Qh4  Bf8  17.Nd6  Bxd6  18.exd6  , followed by Ne5, with a huge initiative. }
16. Bxe7 Rxe7 17. Nd6 Qd7 18. Ng5
{ White gets on with the attack; exploiting the fact that  18.Ng5  h6  now runs into  19.Nh7  Ng6  20.Nxf7  Rxf7  21.Qxg6  with an overwhelming position. }
18... Ng6 19. h4 f5 20. Qf3 Rb8
{ Overlooking the enemy threat.   20...Nxh4  21.Qh5  h6  22.Qxh4  hxg5  23.Qxg5  doesn't help Black's defence much either   So in this case  20...Nf8  was the least of the evils. }
21. Nxh7 Nxe5 { 21...Kxh7  is met by  22.Qh5+  and White wins easily. } 22.
dxe5 Kxh7 23. Nxf5 { This simple shot decides the game at once. } 23... Rf7 24.
Nd6+ Kg8 25. Nxf7 Qxf7 26. Bh7+ Kf8 27. Qxf7+ Kxf7 28. Be4 *

