1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 Bg4
{ Black takes the opportunity to bring out the queen's bishop.   Other popular options are:  4...Bf5  in the same spirit   4...a6  as in Mateuta-Hellsten   4...e6  with a Semi-Slav. }
5. Nc3 e6 6. h3 Bxf3 7. Qxf3 Nbd7 8. Bd2 Bb4
{ A rare move in the Slav, but here it is useful for preventing e3-e4 - besides, in the event of g2-g4 in similar fashion to Sadykov-Sveshnikov, Black can always rely on ...Bxc3 and ...Ne4 if it is needed. }
