[Black "K.Kachiani Gersinska-P.Cramling  German League 2003  Slav Defence"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r2qr1k1/ppbn1ppp/2p2n2/3p4/1P1P4/P1NBPQ1P/3B1PP1/3R1RK1 b - - 0 14"]
[SetUp "1"]

14... Qe7 { Preparing ...Ne4 to seize the centre. } 15. Rfe1 Ne4 16. g3 Ndf6
17. Kg2 a5
{ A pinprick on the queenside, just when White had reinforced her defences on the opposite flank. }
18. Bxe4
{ The pawn that now emerges on  e4  will enhance Black's attack; but after  18.Qe2  axb4  19.axb4  Qe6  , with ideas like ...Ng5, White is also under pressure. }
18... dxe4 19. Qe2 h5 { Preparing ...h5-h4 to soften up the h2-b8 diagonal. }
20. h4 Bd6 21. Rb1 axb4 22. axb4 Qe6
{ Aiming at the light square weaknesses in White's camp. } 23. b5 c5 24. b6
{ Or  24.dxc5  Bxc5  , with the plan ...Qf5 and ...Ng4. } 24... cxd4 25. exd4
Rac8 26. Qb5 Qg4 27. Qe2 Qe6 28. Qb5
{ 28.Rb5  , followed by Rg5, seems preferable, interfering with the enemy attack. }
28... Rc4 { Intercepting the white queen from the kingside defence. } 29. d5
Qc8 30. Rbc1 e3
{ A key move that destroys the white king's shelter and brings the rook on c4 into the attack. }
31. Rxe3
{ 31.Bxe3  failed to  31...Rxc3   While on  31.fxe3  there follows  31...Rxh4  32.gxh4  Qg4+  in similar fashion to the game, with White soon receiving mate. }
31... Rxe3 32. fxe3 Rxh4 33. gxh4 Qg4+
{ In view of  33...Qg4+  34.Kf2  Bg3+  35.Kg2  Bxh4+  36.Kh2  Qg3+  37.Kh1  Qf3+  with mate to come, White resigned. }
