11. b3 { Preparing Ba3 with increased pressure on the enemy camp. } 11... e4
{ After  11...Rd8  12.Ba3  Qe8  13.Qc2  , preparing Rad1, White keeps the initiative; e.g.  13...Nd5  14.Rad1  N7b6  15.Ncxe5  Bxe5  16.Nxe5  Qxe5  17.c4  Bf5  18.e4  Bg4  19.cxd5  Bxd1  20.Rxd1  with a big edge in D.Garcia Illundain-D.Del Rey, Saragossa 1998. }
12. Ba3 Nc5 { Or  12...c5  13.Nd4  , heading for the great square on b5. } 13.
Nd4 b6 14. b4 { Clearing the a3-f8 diagonal for the bishop. } 14... axb4 15.
cxb4 Ne6
{ Since  15...Nxa4  loses material after  16.b5  Nc5  17.Bxc5  , Black has to accept the entrance of the other knight at c6. }
16. Nc6 Qd7 17. b5 Re8 18. Qc2 { Simple and strong, preparing Rad1. } 18... Ng5
19. Rad1 Nh3+ 20. Kh1 Qe6 21. Nd8
{ Tempting; though the prophylactic  21.Ne3  might have been even stronger. }
21... Qf5 22. Ne3 Nxf2+ 23. Kg1 Nh3+
{ Black defended very well up to this point, but here he goes astray. After  23...Nxd1  24.Nxf5  Bxf5  25.Rxd1  Raxd8  the game is far from over. }
24. Bxh3 Qg5 { Or  24...Qxh3  25.Qc6  with double threats at a8 and f6. } 25.
Qb3 { Defence and attack at the same time. The rest is easy. } 25... Bxh3 26.
Qxf7+ Kh8 27. Qxe8+ Nxe8 28. Nf7+ Kg8 29. Nxg5 Bxf1 30. Kxf1
{ Having a piece less, Black resigned. } *

