{ 7.a4  , preventing ...b7-b5, is another direction in this main branch of the Queen's Gambit Accepted. }
7... b5 8. Bb3 Bb7 9. a4 c4
{ A dubious choice, since releasing the tension at d4 implies that White will have free hands in the centre.   9...b4  , followed by ...Nbd7, was better. }
