[Result "*"]
[FEN "r4rk1/1q1pbppp/p1n1p3/1p2P3/4NQ2/4B1P1/PPP2P1P/R3R1K1 b - - 0 15"]
[SetUp "1"]

15... f6
{ By this pawn break Black fights against the enemy centre and clears the f-file for a future attack.   15...Qc7  was less promising due to  16.Bc5  Bxc5  17.Nxc5  Ne7  18.b4  . }
16. exf6 Bxf6 17. Nxf6+ Rxf6 18. Qd6
{ White prepares Rad1, but Black's reply finishes off this idea at once.  18.Qe4  was correct, when  18...d5  19.Qg2  Ne5  20.Bf4  Ng6  21.Bg5  Rf5  , preparing ...e5-e4 and ...Ne5, keeps the initiative. }
18... Rf5 { With the dual intention of 19...Ne5 and 19...Rd5. } 19. Bf4
{ Now the knight enters on d4 instead with strong effect.   19.f4  Rd5  20.Qa3  was more solid. }
19... Rd5 20. Qa3
{ Or  20.Qc7  Qxc7  21.Bxc7  Rc8  with ...Ne5 or ...Nd4 next. } 20... Nd4 21.
Qd3 Rf8 22. Re4
{ Overlooking Black's next move. The last chance was  22.Qe4  , when  22...g5  23.c3  Nc6  24.Be3  Ne5  keeps the initiative. }
22... e5 23. c4
{ Both  23.Bxe5  and  23.Rd1  lose straight away to  23...Nf3+   While  23.Rxe5  Rxe5  24.Qxd4  Re2  is also hopeless for White - Atlas. }
23... bxc4 24. Qxc4 Rc8 25. Qa4 Rd6
{ In view of the imminent material losses, White resigned. } *

