1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Ne4
{ Quite an optimistic move, which is convincingly dealt with by Alekhine in this game. }
4. Nfd2
{ 4.g3  also made sense whereas  4.Nbd2  f5  5.Nxe4  fxe4  , with 6...d5 next, is less ambitious. }
4... Bb4
{ In contrast,  4...f5  5.Nxe4  fxe4  6.Nc3  d5  7.Bf4  now yields White a pleasant advantage.   With  4...Bb4  Marshall accelerates his development and also sets the little trap  5.a3  Qf6  . }
5. Qc2 { Increasing the pressure on e4 and enabling 6. Nc3. } 5... d5 6. Nc3 f5
