{ An interesting reply to the sharp 4. f3 variation. Black prepares to meet c4xd5 by ...c6xd5 at any moment, thus maintaining an excellent pawn structure. As for the 'bad' bishop on c8, it can be activated by ...b7-b6 and ...Ba6. }
7. Qc2
{ An ambitious try, preparing e2-e4. Another direction is  7.e3  O-O  8.Bd3  b6  9.Ne2  Ba6  with a complex battle. }
7... O-O 8. cxd5
{ The immediate  8.e4  can be dealt with in the same way as in the game, starting with  8...dxe4  . }
8... cxd5 9. e4 dxe4 10. fxe4
