1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. Re1 Nf6 6. c3
{ Another main direction is  6.e5  Nd5  7.Nc3  , a line that makes some Black players prefer 5...e5 instead. }
6... O-O 7. d4 d5 8. exd5
{ 8.e5  Ne4  9.Bxc6  bxc6  10.Nbd2  is more ambitious, trying to get a grip on the dark squares. }
8... Qxd5 9. c4 Qd6 10. d5 Nd4
{ The most active choice; exploiting the fact that   10...Nd4  11.Nxd4  cxd4  12.Qxd4  runs into  12...Ng4  . }
11. Nxd4 cxd4 12. h3
{ White will soon have to pay for his slow development.  12.Nd2  , followed by Nf3, was essential, when Black could react just like in the game. }
12... --
