1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. f4
{ In the previous century this line was quite popular against the Najdorf; whereas nowadays White tends to prefer  6.Be3  or  6.Bg5  . }
6... Qc7 7. Be2
{ After this move the battle becomes similar to the 6. Be2 variation.   7.Bd3  was more in the spirit of the set-up with f2-f4 while the restrictive  7.a4  can also be considered. }
7... e5 8. Nb3 b5 9. a3 Bb7 10. Bf3 Nbd7 11. O-O Be7 12. Kh1 O-O 13. g4
{ After standard moves from both sides, White finally commences actions on the kingside.   13.Qe1  , heading for g3, was also possible. }
