1. c4
{ In a normal Benko after  1.d4  Nf6  2.c4  c5  3.d5  b5  4.cxb5  a6  ,  5.e4  would obviously have failed to  5...Nxe4  . }
1... g6 2. d4 c5 3. d5 b5
{ This version of the Benko Gambit doesn't work too well, as we will see next. }
4. cxb5 a6 5. e4 { A natural move that yields White swift development. } 5...
axb5
{ 5...Bg7  was more flexible, waiting with ...a6xb5 until White moves his king's bishop - Hjartarson. }
6. Bxb5 Bg7 7. Ne2
