11. f4
{ Preparing a pawn break with e4-e5, in order to open the position before Black is properly developed. }
11... Nf6 12. e5 dxe5
{ Or  12...Nd7  13.e6  fxe6  14.dxe6  Nf6  15.f5  with a strong attack - Hjartarson. }
13. fxe5 Nd7
{ In the event of  13...Ng4  , Hjartarson had planned  14.e6  fxe6  15.Nf4  Bd4+  16.Kh1  Nf2+  17.Rxf2  Bxf2  18.Nxe6  Nc7  19.Qf3  with strong threats. }
14. e6 fxe6 15. Bg5
{ Some mobilization before capturing on e6.   Less convincing was  15.dxe6  Nf6  , followed by ...O-O   Or  15.Nf4  Bd4+  16.Kh1  O-O  . }
15... Nf6 16. Nf4 { Again White is attentive to the opponent's castling. }
16... Nc7
{ Now  16...O-O  runs into  17.Nxe6  Rf7  18.d6  with decisive threats. } 17.
d6 exd6 18. Nxe6
{ A strong temporary sacrifice that further exposes Black's king.   18.Qxd6  Ra6  was less clear. }
18... Nxe6 19. Qe2 { Of course not  19.Bxf6  O-O  . } 19... Kd7
{ Now, on the other hand,  19...O-O  drops a piece after  20.Qxe6+  , so Black's king is forced to stay in the centre. }
20. Bxf6 Rhf8 21. Ne4 Kc7 22. Bxg7 Nxg7 23. Rxf8 Rxf8 24. Nxd6
{ Luring the king to a decisive double attack. } 24... Kxd6 25. Rd1+ Kc6 26.
Qe4+ Kb5 27. Qd3+ c4 28. Qd5+
{ In view of  28.Qd5+  Ka6   @@StartBracket@@or  28...Kb6  29.Qd6+  @@EndBracket@@  29.Qxc4+  Kb6  30.Rd6+  Kb7  31.Rd7+  Kb8  32.Qb3+  with mate, Black resigned - Hjartarson. }
