14... g5
{ An excellent flank advance to gain space and undermine the d4-pawn by ...g5-g4. }
15. Bc3 g4 16. Ne1 f6
{ A timely pawn break;   by which Black exploits the fact that  16...f6  17.exf6  Qxf6  leads to strong pressure at d4. }
17. Bd3 fxe5 18. Bxf5 { 18.dxe5  d4  19.Bxf5  exf5  comes to the same thing. }
18... exf5 19. dxe5 d4 20. Bb4
{ Thanks to his superior activity Black is already a bit better, since   20.Bxd4  fails fatally to  20...Nxd4  21.Qxd4  Bb5  . }
20... Nxb4 21. axb4 Bb5 22. Rg1 b6
{ Restricting the knight on a4.   22...Bxb4  23.Nc2  was less clear. } 23. Nc2
d3 24. Ne3 f4 25. Nxg4
{ Desperation.  After   25.Nf5  Qd7  26.Nd6+  Bxd6  27.exd6  Qxd6  28.Nc3  Bc6  Black keeps the initiative, but the battle goes on. }
25... hxg4 26. Qxg4 Rc7
