[White "Exercises Chapter 3"]
[Black "M.Dvoretsky-J.Klovans  USSR Championship,  Yerevan 1975  Vienna Game "]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1b2r2/pp4pk/1npb1q1p/4p3/P4p2/1QPP1NP1/2P2PBP/1RB1R1K1 w - - 0 16"]
[SetUp "1"]

16. Ba3
{ By an indirect attack on the e5-pawn, White makes the enemy attack less likely to succeed. }
16... c5
{ Black prevents the bishop exchange but also weakens the light squares in his camp.   16...Bxa3  17.Qxa3  fxg3  18.fxg3  Bh3  was preferable - Dvoretsky, although after the simple  19.Rf1  Bxg2  20.Kxg2  , followed by Rbe1, White keeps some advantage thanks to his superior pawn structure. }
17. a5 c4
{ Just as on the previous move,  17...Be6  18.c4  only yields Black an additional problem with the b7-pawn   While  17...Nd7  18.Nh4  , preparing Be4+, is also awkward for him. }
18. Qa2 Bxa3 19. Qxa3 Nd7 20. Qb4
{ 20.d4  exd4  21.Nxd4  was even stronger - Zlotnik. } 20... cxd3 21. cxd3
{ By now White's superiority in piece activity is striking. } 21... Kh8 22. Qb5
{ More technical than  22.Nxe5  Nxe5  23.Rxe5  fxg3  24.fxg3  Bh3  - Zlotnik. }
22... Rb8 23. Nxe5 Nxe5 24. Qxe5 fxg3 25. fxg3
{ With a sound extra pawn and more active pieces, White is winning.   There followed  25.fxg3  Qf2+  26.Kh1  Bd7  27.Rf1  Qc2  28.Qd6  Rfd8  29.Rxb7  Rxb7  30.Bxb7  and Black resigned. }
