1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. Nf3 g6 5. Bc4 Nb6 6. Bb3 Bg7 7. O-O
{ 7.Ng5  , followed by Qf3 or f2-f4, is a more aggressive approach. } 7... O-O
{ 7...Bg4  didn't work yet due to  8.Bxf7+  . } 8. h3
{ Preventing 8...Bg4.   In contrast,  8.Qe2  Bg4  9.e6  is strongly met by  9...d5  10.exf7+  Rxf7  11.Nbd2  Nc6  12.c3  e5  and Black seizes the initiative. }
8... Nc6 9. Qe2 Na5
{ A typical idea in the Alekhine, in order to reduce White's attacking potential by a timely swap on b3. }
10. Bg5 d5 11. c3
