[White "Exercises Chapter 3"]
[Black "S.Sulskis-A.Galkin  European Championship,  Batumi 2002  Caro-Kann Defence "]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6 2. c4 d5 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. exd5 Nf6
{ Since  4...Qxd5  5.Nc3  , followed by d2-d4, yields White a favourable version of mainstream IQP positions, Black prepares to recapture on d5 with the knight. }
5. Qa4+
{ This check obstructs Black so that he can't easily recover the d5-pawn.   In the same spirit,  5.Bb5+  is also possible. }
5... Nbd7 6. Nc3 g6 7. g4
{ A highly aggressive way of treating this system.   More common is  7.Nf3  Bg7  8.Bc4  O-O  9.d3  , hanging on to the pawn. }
7... Bg7 8. g5 Nh5 9. Nge2 O-O 10. Ng3
{ White doesn't hide his intentions: clear the h-file for a future attack on the enemy king, supported by a timely Qh4.Your move... @@StartBracket@@The exercise starts on the next variation@@EndBracket@@ }
