Qxd4
{ An oversight in a difficult position.   17...Nxd4  was equally bad due to  18.Rad1  e5  19.Rxd4  exd4  20.Qxc7  with decisive threats   While after  17...Bd7  18.a4  Qxd4  19.Rfc1  Qxc4  20.Rxc4  Nd6  21.Rxc7  White keeps a huge advantage. }
18. Bc6+
{ A nice blow which converts White's initiative into something more tangible. }
18... Bd7
