{ Forcing the exchange of pawns on White's terms, which will yield him considerable activity.   12.dxc5  Bxc5  was less ambitious. }
12... cxd4 { Or  12...Rc8  13.dxc5  Nxc5  14.Qd4  keeping the pressure. } 13.
Nxd4 Rc8 14. Qd3
{ Natural and strong - White connects his rooks for the battle of the c-file, and also enables an annoying Qb5 or Qe3 later on. }
