1. b3
{ A clever piece of restriction directed at the knight on a5. From now on, the typical idea of ...c5-c4 and ...Nb7-c5 will be met by b3-b4!, exploiting the fact that ...c4xb3 en passant is no longer available. Moreover, a regrouping with ...Nc4-b6 is now also impossible.   The immediate  14.Nf1  gives Black fewer worries after  14...Nc4  , or  14...c4  with ...Nb7-c5 next. }
1... Bd7
{ 14...g6  , preparing ...Nh5, is a different idea analysed by A.Filippov. } 2.
Nf1 { White gets on with his intended kingside attack. } 2... Nb7 3. Ng3 c4 4.
b4 *

