{ Milov's play in this game is very logical, and teaches us something about priorities in chess. Three moves ago it was worth a pawn to keep restricting the opponent's forces, whereas on this occasion, he has no concern about surrendering the bishop pair in order to eliminate the opponent's most active piece.   22.Rad1  Nc2  was less convincing. }
