1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. b4 Bxb4 5. c3 Ba5
{ 5...Be7  6.d4  Na5  is another popular reply to the Evans Gambit. } 6. d4
exd4 7. O-O d6
{ 7...Nge7  , followed by 8...d5, is supposed to be Black's best try   Whereas  7...dxc3  8.Qb3  Qe7  9.Nxc3  Nf6  10.e5  yields White a crushing attack. }
8. cxd4 Bb6 9. Nc3 Nf6
{ Quite an indifferent move, as if this was a quiet Italian.   After  9...Nge7  10.Ng5  , with the idea  10...O-O  11.Qh5  , Black is also in great danger;   So  9...Na5  was called for, when  10.Bd3  Ne7  , followed by ...O-O, should be playable for him. }
10. e5
{ Clearing lines towards the enemy king.   10.Bg5  h6  was less convincing. }
10... dxe5
