[SetUp "1"]

11. Ba3
{ Preventing Black's castling is White's main priority here.   11.Re1  O-O   And  11.d5  Na5  are less powerful. }
11... Bxd4
{ After  11...Nxd4  12.Nxe5  Be6  13.Re1  c5  14.Qa4+  Kf8  15.Rad1  White had a strong initiative in J.Blackburne-NN, Great Britain @@StartBracket@@ simul @@EndBracket@@ 1872. }
12. Qb3 Be6
{ An early surrender; but  12...Qd7  13.Ng5  Nd8  14.Rad1  is also depressing for Black. }
13. Bxe6 fxe6 14. Qxe6+ Ne7 15. Nxd4 exd4 16. Rfe1 Ng8 17. Nd5
{ Recovering the material with a clear advantage.   The game continued  17.Nd5  Qd7  18.Bxe7   @@StartBracket@@  18.Qe5  won outright@@EndBracket@@  Qxe6  19.Rxe6  Kd7  20.Rae1   @@StartBracket@@  20.Bc5  won a pawn@@EndBracket@@  Re8  21.R6e4  c6  22.Rxd4  cxd5  23.Rxd5+  Kc6  24.Rd6+  Kc7  25.Rc1+  Kb8  26.Bh4  Nh6  27.Bg3  Ka8  28.h3  Nf5  29.Rd7  and White went on to win. }
