[SetUp "1"]

13. Qb4
{ Keeping the enemy king in the centre.   13.Rfe1+  Kf8  , followed by ...Kg8, is less convincing  though   13.Qc5  is a good alternative; e.g.  13...Qd7  14.Rfe1+  Kd8  15.d6  Qc6  16.Qd4  with a huge advantage - Botvinnik. }
13... Qd7 { A clumsy move, but the d8-square was badly needed by the king. }
14. Nb5 Kd8 15. Rac1 { With the devastating threat of 16. Rc7. } 15... a5
{ Neither  15...Qxd5  16.Nc7  ;   Nor  15...Bf8  16.Qd4  was any better for Black. }
16. Qc5 Ra6 17. Na7
{ A technical choice, by which White secures a decisive material advantage. }
17... Rxa7 18. Qb6+ Ke8 19. Rfe1+ Kf8 20. Qxa7 Bh6 21. Qc5+ Kg7 22. Rcd1
{ There followed  22.Rcd1  Qa4  23.Rxd3  Qxa2  24.Qd4  Rd8  25.d6  b5  26.Qb6  Rd7  27.Qxb5  and Black resigned, in view of  27...Rb7  28.Qxb7  Bxb7  29.d7  . }
