[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 d6 4. Nf3 Nxe4 5. d4 d5 6. Bd3 Bd6 7. O-O O-O 8. c4
Nf6
{ A surprising retreat of Black's most active piece.   Practice sees  8...c6  almost invariably here, keeping the presence in the centre. }
9. c5 Be7 10. Qc2
{ 10.Qc2  prepares to meet  10...Bg4  by  11.Ne5  .   Other logical reactions are  10.Ne5  , seizing the centre, and the restrictive  10.h3  . }
10... b6
{ A badly timed attack on White's pawn chain.   10...Nc6  , speeding up development, was preferable. }
11. --
