[SetUp "1"]

11. Qa4+
{ A timely check that deprives Black of castling. For this reason, 10...Nd7 was preferable last turn, when 11. Qa4 Bb7, preparing ...a7-a6 and ...b6-b5, is quite acceptable for him - Gershon. }
11... Kf8 12. e4
{ With the enemy king stuck in the centre, it makes sense to the open the position. }
12... Qe8
{ Quite a desperate choice - Black sacrifices the d5-pawn in order to swap queens.   12...Bxf1  13.Kxf1  Bxe5  14.dxe5  Nd7  was preferable, although White keeps the pressure after  15.exd5  Nxe5  16.Rd1  - Gershon. }
13. Qxe8+ Kxe8 14. exd5 exd5 15. Bg2 Bxe5
{ Or  15...Bb7  16.Nxd5  , followed by Nc4. } 16. Bxd5 Bxd4 17. O-O-O Bxf2 18.
Bxa8
{ With both a material and positional superiority White is winning.   There followed  18.Bxa8  f6  19.Kb1   @@StartBracket@@  19.Ne4  , heading for d6, was stronger - Gershon@@EndBracket@@  19...Bc5  20.Bd5  g6  21.Bb3  Kf8  22.Ne4  Be7  23.Rhe1  and Black's position remained very difficult, although incredibly enough, he eventually won the game! }
