[SetUp "1"]

13. Bh6
{ A key move that prevents Black from castling while connecting the major pieces. }
13... e5
{ Black aims at liberating himself by ...e5-e4 and ...Ne5, but after White's reply he will hardly be able to move.   The last chance was  13...Ng8  14.Bg5  Ngf6  , insisting on the castling - Giardelli, when  15.Nf4  O-O  16.Qe2  keeps a strong initiative. }
14. Qa4 Kd8
{ There is nothing better; e.g.  14...e4  15.Rae1  , followed by 16. Nf2;   Or  14...Ng8  15.Bg5  Nf6  16.Bxb7  . }
15. Qa5+ { Provoking new weaknesses. } 15... b6 16. Qa4 e4 17. Qc6 Rb8 18. Bf4
Ne5
{ This loses outright.   18...exf3  drops the queen after  19.Bc7+  Ke8  20.Rae1   but  18...Bb7  was more tenacious, when one good reply is  19.Qc7+  Ke8  20.Rae1  h6  21.Nf2  Qe6  22.Bd6  , with the devastating threat of  22...--  23.Nxe4  Nxe4  24.Bxe4  Bxe4  25.Rf4  . }
19. Rad1+ Bd7 20. Bxe5 Qxe5 21. Bg4
{ In view of heavy material losses, Black resigned. } *

