[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c5 4. Nf3 Nc6
{ A sharper battle arises after  4...cxd4  5.Nxd4  e5  6.Ndb5  a6   @@StartBracket@@or  6...d4  7.Nd5  @@EndBracket@@  7.Qa4  . }
5. Bf4 Nf6 6. e3
{ White is applying a modest, but fully playable line against the Tarrasch. }
6... cxd4 7. Nxd4 Nxd4
{ 7...Be7  or  7...Bb4  was preferable, speeding up development, since  8.Nxc6  bxc6  at any moment just helps Black in reinforcing her centre. }
8. Qxd4 Be7 9. Rd1
{ Stepping up the pressure at d5.   A good alternative was  9.cxd5  exd5  10.Bb5+  Bd7  11.Bxd7+  Qxd7  12.O-O  , with a slight but enduring advantage in this simplified IQP position. }
9... --
