1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Bf5 5. Ng3 Bg6 6. Bc4
{ An aggressive line against the Classical Caro-Kann. White intends N1e2 @@StartBracket@@h3@@EndBracket@@ -f4 next, after which he could either harass the bishop on g6 by h2-h4, or prepare a sacrifice on e6, while this game features a third plan with f2-f4.   The main line goes  6.h4  h6  7.Nf3  Nd7  8.h5  Bh7  9.Bd3  with a heavy theoretical battle. }
6... e6 7. N1e2 Nf6 8. O-O
{ 8.Nf4  is another option, when Black often replies  8...Bd6  , followed by 9...Qc7, in order to challenge the knight on f4. }
8... Nbd7 9. f4
{ Intending f4-f5 to clear the f-file and the a2-g8 diagonal towards Black's king. }
9... Nb6 10. Bd3 Bxd3 11. Qxd3
{ Your move... @@StartBracket@@The exercise starts on the next variation@@EndBracket@@ }
