[SetUp "1"]

8... a6
{ An essential move that parries the dangerous plan of b4-b5.   In contrast,  8...e6  9.b4  Be7  10.b5  O-O  11.b4  , intending 12. bxc6 and 13. b5, yields White a favourable structure on the queenside   and even  8...e5  is well met by  9.b4 }
9. Nh4
{ Now if  9.b4  , then simply  9...Rc8  or  9...Rd8  , finishing off the b4-b5 idea. }
9... Bc2 10. b4 Rd8 11. Kd2 Bg6
{ Black has nothing to worry about.   There followed  11...Bg6  12.f4  e6  13.Nxg6  hxg6  14.Be2  Be7  15.Kc2  Ne4  16.Nxe4  dxe4  17.Bd2  Nf6  18.h4  Nd5  19.g3  Kd7  20.Ra3  g5  21.fxg5  Bxg5  22.Rf1  Bf6  , intending ...Ke7 and ...g5, with a slight initiative that Hertneck later converted into a win. }
