[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3
{ White's set-up in this game can also be initiated by  3.g3  , with the point that after  3...d5  4.cxd5  Nxd5  5.Bg2  Bg7  6.e4  , Black lacks the option of 6...Nxc3. }
3... d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. g3 Bg7 6. Bg2 Nxc3
{ Anyway,  6...Nb6  is perfectly possible as well. } 7. bxc3 c5 8. e3 Nc6
{ 8...Qa5  9.Bd2  O-O  10.Ne2  Nc6  11.O-O  Rd8  is another popular set-up. }
9. Ne2 Bd7
{ Black hurries to start action on the queenside, his traditional battlefield in the Grünfeld.   Of course,  9...O-O  is also possible. }
10. O-O Rc8 11. Rb1 cxd4
{ 11...b6  or  11...Na5  was preferable - Lundin. We will soon see the difference. }
12. cxd4 b6
