[Black "A.Khalifman-V.Filippov  Russian Team Championship 1995  Semi-Slav Defence"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nc3 e6 4. e4 dxe4 5. Nxe4 Bb4+ 6. Bd2 Qxd4 7. Bxb4 Qxe4+
{ A sharp branch of the Slav, that we saw earlier in Volkov-Kempinski and Flear-Vera. }
8. Be2 Ne7 { Quite a rare alternative to the more frequent 8...Na6. } 9. Qd2
{ The main idea behind Black's previous move was to meet  9.Nf3  by  9...Nd5  , but even so, after  10.Nd2  Qd4  11.Ba3  Nf4  12.O-O  White has had good results in practice. Anyway, the text rules out this idea by protecting the bishop on b4. }
9... Ng6
{ Both  9...Qxg2  10.O-O-O  Nd7  11.Nf3   and  9...c5  10.Bxc5  Nbc6  11.Nf3  O-O  12.O-O-O  clearly favour White - Khalifman. }
10. --
