16. a4
{ White is aware that the opponent intends 16...Bb5, and so prevents it.   Now the knight on b8 becomes a problem for Black, since after  16.a4  bxa3  17.Rxa3  he can't play 17...Bb5 anyway. }
16... Kd8
{ 16...Kd8  prepares to meet  17.Nc4  with  17...Re8  , but Yusupov sticks to his original plan. }
17. g3 Bg4 18. Ne3 Bf3 19. e5 { Clearing the long diagonal for the bishop. }
19... dxe5 20. Nxf3 Qxf3 21. Bg2 Qf6 22. d6 Ra7 23. O-O
{ By now Black is in big trouble due to his uncoordinated forces and the exposed king on d8. }
23... Ng7
{ Or  23...Nd7  24.Nd5  , when both  24...Qg7   @@StartBracket@@and  24...Qxd6  25.Rfd1  @@EndBracket@@  25.Qe3  , preparing 26. Ne7, clearly favour White. }
24. Rac1 Nd7 25. Rfd1 Nf5
{ After  25...Ne6  26.Nd5  Qg5  27.Qxg5+  Nxg5  28.Ne7  , with the threat of Nc6+, Black is done - Yusupov. }
26. Nxf5 Qxf5 27. Qe3 { The threat of 28. Rxc5 proves decisive. } 27... e4 28.
Bxe4 Qe5 29. Rd5 Qe6 30. Rdxc5 Nxc5 31. Qxc5 *

