14. a5
{ Diverting the black queen from the sixth rank so that a sacrifice with Bxe6 or Nxe6 becomes possible. }
14... Qxa5
{ 14...Qc7  is strongly met by  15.Bxe6  while after   14...Qb7  15.Nxe6  fxe6  16.Bxe6  d4  17.Qxd4  Nc6  18.Qd2  Ndxe5  19.Bd5  , followed by Rfe1, White also enjoys a strong initiative. }
15. Bxe6 fxe6 16. Nxe6 g6
{ Now the second white knight joins the battle with great effect.   A lesser evil was  16...Kf7  17.Nd4  Nc5  18.Qf3  with compensation for White - Nisipeanu/Stoica. }
17. Nc3 Qxa1
{ Or  17...Qb6  18.Ng7+  Kf7  19.Nxd5  Qd8  20.Nf5  gxf5  21.Qh5+  , when both  21...Ke6   @@StartBracket@@and  21...Kg8  22.e6  @@EndBracket@@  22.Nxe7  Qxe7  23.Rad1  , followed by Rd6+, lead to a devastating attack. }
18. Qxa1 bxc3 19. Qa5 Nc6
{ After  19...cxb2  20.Nc7+  Rxc7  21.Qxc7  O-O  22.e6  White is also winning. }
20. Qxd5 Nb4 21. Qd4 Rb7 22. bxc3
{ With Black's forces in disorder and his king still exposed, the rest is easy for White. }
22... Nxc2 23. Qc4 Nb6 24. Nc7+ Kd8 25. Rd1+ Bd7 26. Qe4 Rxc7 27. e6 *

