[FEN "2kr3r/1bq2pp1/pp1ppn1p/2b1n3/2P1PB2/PNN2P2/1P1Q2PP/1K1R1B1R w - - 0 16"]
[SetUp "1"]

16. h4
{ Before taking aggressive action, Kasparov limits the opponent's intended plan of ...g7-g5.   In contrast, after  16.Be2  g5  17.Bg3  Nh5  Black obtains some counterplay on the dark squares. }
16... Kb8 17. h5 { 17.Be2  Nh5  18.Bh2  Bf2  was less precise - Kasparov. }
17... Rd7
{ A typical Hedgehog pawn break with  17...d5  fails to  18.exd5  exd5  19.Nxc5  bxc5  20.Qe1  Rhe8  21.cxd5  - Kasparov, so Black can only wait while the opponent improves his position little by little. }
18. Rc1 Rc8 19. Be2 Ka7 20. Rhd1 Rdd8 21. g4
{ By now White is better across the whole board. } 21... Ng8 22. Bg3 Ne7 23. f4
N5c6 24. Bf3 Rb8 25. Bh4 Rd7
{ This lets White launch a spectacular combination.   25...Rbc8  was more solid, after which Kasparov intended the space-gaining  26.g5  . }
26. Nb5+ axb5 27. cxb5 Na5
{ Losing outright; but after  27...Rc8  28.bxc6  Nxc6  29.e5  Black is also in huge trouble. }
28. Nxa5 bxa5 29. Rxc5 { The drawback to Black's 25th move becomes evident. }
29... dxc5 30. Qxd7 Qxf4 31. Rd6
{ In view of  31.Rd6  Ka8  32.Qc7  Bxe4+  33.Bxe4+  Qxe4+  34.Ka1  , renewing the threat of 35 Ra6 mate, Black resigned. }
